The paper deals with the problem of locomotion for humanoid robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel approach that combines model-based policies with machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also incorporates a Control Barrier Function (CBF) process to ensure safety during learning, which suggests that the paper could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses footstep features, which could involve computer vision techniques, suggesting that the paper could also be classified under computer vision (cs.CV).
